Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.87,0:02:21.66,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Now the chaos of the start has settled down, \Nthe order has taken shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.05,0:02:35.57,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,These 15 fighting machines scale the \Nsteep slopes of Sector 1 at full throttle!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.98,0:03:03.45,Default,Otani,0000,0000,0000,,Going on the attack already, Aiba?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.69,0:03:09.12,Default,Otani,0000,0000,0000,,But if you get too keyed up, \None bad call can sink your whole race.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.67,0:03:11.51,Italics,Otani,0000,0000,0000,,That's how it is in MFG.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.61,0:03:16.65,Italics,Otani,0000,0000,0000,,And after three years of doing this, \NI finally feel like I can be competitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.21,0:03:19.80,Italics,Otani,0000,0000,0000,,Experience is everything in MFG.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.85,0:03:36.59,Italics,Second,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Daigo? \NYou're getting left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.59,0:03:40.69,Default,Oishi,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell do you {\i1}think{\i0} is wrong?\NI can't stamp on the gas like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.13,0:03:44.41,Default,Oishi,0000,0000,0000,,If only I had slightly bigger tires...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.41,0:03:47.91,Default,Oishi,0000,0000,0000,,Damned grip-to-weight ratio rule!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.24,0:03:58.47,Default,Oishi,0000,0000,0000,,I spent a lot of money \Nto bring a fast car here...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.84,0:04:01.67,Default,Oishi,0000,0000,0000,,So just let me floor it, damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.70,0:04:19.37,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,In simplistic terms, you can interpret \Nthe standardized grip-to-weight ratio rule
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.37,0:04:23.07,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,as a way of standardizing cornering speeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.07,0:04:28.94,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Regulating only the grip-to-weight ratio of the\Ncars and not the body or engine displacement...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.94,0:04:32.33,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,I still remember the shock \NI felt when I heard that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.33,0:04:38.04,Default,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,Right. It's such a simple touch, but one that's\N hard to pin down the reasoning behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.04,0:04:41.28,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,But since there's little \Nto be gained in the corners,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:41.28,0:04:45.01,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,the more powerful cars \Nseemingly have the advantage,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.55,0:04:46.51,Default,Signs,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial Black\bord0\shad0\fay0.04\blur0.3\fs28\fscx85\c&H3A322B&\move(511.333,112,479.333,-14)}Maezono Kazuhiro
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.55,0:04:46.51,Default,Signs,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial Black\bord0\shad0\fay0.04\blur0.3\fs28\fscx85\c&H3A322B&\move(504,241.333,472,115.333)}Kitahara Nozomi
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.55,0:04:46.51,Default,Signs,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial Black\bord0\shad0\fay0.04\blur0.3\fs28\fscx85\c&H3A322B&\move(502,366,470,240)}Katagiri Kanata
Dialogue: 1,0:04:45.01,0:04:47.70,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,because they can accelerate\N better on the straights.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.70,0:04:51.47,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,And that's why we've seen an arms\N race on the power front, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.75,0:04:56.56,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly. Premium high-end European \Nmodels have dominated the top spots,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.56,0:04:59.40,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,giving the rule its nickname:\Nthe rich man's regulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.98,0:05:03.99,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,But I think we may be approaching \Na turning point in that way of thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.49,0:05:05.57,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,How do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.36,0:05:10.81,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,After Michael Beckenbauer \Njoined the competition last year,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.81,0:05:13.70,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,we've seen a shift from \Npure power to a balanced setup.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.35,0:05:18.59,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,The rookie, Katagiri Kanata, is the \Nperfect example of this school of thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.53,0:05:27.80,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,Granted, his car is so down on power, \Nit can hardly be called well-balanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.18,0:05:31.26,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Well, {\i1}excuse{\i0} me. \NAs if I don't already know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.97,0:05:37.95,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,This regulation Ryo Takahashi put in has \Nsuch exact specifications on tire durability,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.95,0:05:45.36,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,it makes me think the possibility of upsets \Nwas intentional and always part of the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.32,0:05:51.89,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,I'm honestly kind of speechless\Nat how brilliantly set up it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.23,0:05:58.58,Italics,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like Kogashiwa learned \Nsomething in all those years of racing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.05,0:06:00.83,Italics,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,He's on the right track.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.40,0:06:04.43,Italics,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,MFG is the next phase in \Nthe evolution of Project D.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.43,0:06:08.60,Italics,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,What Ryosuke called his "study of \Nhigh-speed racing on public roads."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.59,0:06:16.15,Italics,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,But I have doubts that anyone can solve this\N complex formula Ryosuke has come up with.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.53,0:06:21.98,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The leaders are coming up\N to the rest house.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.46,0:06:28.36,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Aiba in the 9 is gunning\N for Sakamoto in the 5!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.36,0:06:30.66,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,You can't take your eyes off this tussle!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.00,0:06:34.62,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it. I'm not letting \Nsome European car beat me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.03,0:06:38.71,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Let's show 'em the old Yamato spirit, GTR.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.38,0:06:42.47,Italics,Sakamoto,0000,0000,0000,,Aiba, if you're too aggressive \Non a freaky course like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.47,0:06:45.96,Italics,Sakamoto,0000,0000,0000,,you'll be dead a couple of times over.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.96,0:06:50.89,Italics,Sakamoto,0000,0000,0000,,With my huge engine displacement, 4WD,\Nand electronic control, I'm decked out for war!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.89,0:06:54.05,Italics,Sakamoto,0000,0000,0000,,I let the car take me around \Nthe corners, then I blast away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.43,0:06:57.64,Italics,Sakamoto,0000,0000,0000,,Because in MFG, your car is everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.73,0:07:06.19,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The racers make their way \Nout of Sector 1 and into Sector 2!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.96,0:07:11.17,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,And after that steep climb \Ncomes the downhill descent!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.17,0:07:16.12,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,What changes will we see to the order\Nas the cars exit the power section?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.70,0:07:26.05,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,So far, 14 cars have passed the rest house.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.05,0:07:30.05,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The 86 is a bit further back, \Nbut catching fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.35,0:07:33.68,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,And now, all the cars have entered Sector 2!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.04,0:07:35.64,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Ogata here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.64,0:07:37.93,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Oil temperature and pressure look good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.93,0:07:40.17,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,And your fuel's where it should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.17,0:07:41.35,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Anything you need?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.58,0:07:45.07,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Ogata-san, could you tell me \Nhow far it is to the car in front?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.54,0:07:47.07,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see it anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.07,0:07:49.41,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,The car in front? Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.41,0:07:51.35,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,That's the 18, the Alfa Romeo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.35,0:07:53.52,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,It's 6.8 seconds up the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.52,0:07:55.78,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Roger. I'm going after them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.26,0:08:02.46,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,That's easy to say, man. 6.8 seconds \Nis a decent chunk of time to make up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.38,0:08:13.68,Default,Kakeru,0000,0000,0000,,Kakeru here. What are you doing, Nozomi?\NGet past that Honda and catch up already.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.06,0:08:18.56,Default,Nozomi,0000,0000,0000,,He's tougher than you'd think. Despite being\N an FF, he's really fast out of the corners.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.78,0:08:20.52,Default,Nozomi,0000,0000,0000,,I could use a hand, bro.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.82,0:08:22.63,Default,Kakeru,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I'll have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.63,0:08:26.94,Default,Kakeru,0000,0000,0000,,Keep an eye out for a chance to do \Nthe thing. We'll go with Formation #3.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.94,0:08:30.15,Default,Nozomi,0000,0000,0000,,Copy that. I'm counting on you, big bro.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.95,0:08:40.91,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,I've caught up. The FK8 has better \Nstability when going downhill.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.91,0:08:43.82,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,That Lotus Exige ain't so hot after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.82,0:08:45.33,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave you in the dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.92,0:08:47.71,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,Your outside's wide open!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.13,0:08:49.62,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.06,0:08:58.01,Default,Kakeru,0000,0000,0000,,Now! Get in there, Nozomi!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.75,0:09:01.34,Default,Nozomi,0000,0000,0000,,See ya later!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.72,0:09:07.48,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,What is this crap? He left the door open\Njust to bait me into making a move?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.48,0:09:10.76,Italics,Second,0000,0000,0000,,Watch out, Maezono. There's one on your tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.76,0:09:13.69,Default,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,You're too late! The Alfa already got past me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.69,0:09:14.59,Italics,Second,0000,0000,0000,,Not her!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.82,0:09:22.45,Default,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,Do your job, booth! If the 86 had caught up,\N you should've said something!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.45,0:09:23.60,Italics,Second,0000,0000,0000,,I just did!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.60,0:09:25.68,Default,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,If he's already here, you took too long!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.68,0:09:28.18,Default,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,My eyes are on what's in front, damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.06,0:09:33.77,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,But I thought the 86 was way back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.77,0:09:39.85,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,The second we hit the downhill, he ate up\Nthe gap. What kind of trick did he use?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.34,0:09:44.27,Italics,Nozomi,0000,0000,0000,,The 86 is behind us, bro. Kanata's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.27,0:09:49.43,Default,Kakeru,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it. We don't stand a chance \Nin a fair fight in the technical section.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.43,0:09:50.90,Default,Kakeru,0000,0000,0000,,Let's gap him as much as we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.13,0:09:54.21,Default,Nozomi,0000,0000,0000,,Gotcha. Things are getting \Npretty fun now, huh, bro?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.21,0:09:56.15,Italics,Kakeru,0000,0000,0000,,Not even a little!
