Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.68,0:15:58.93,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,the 8 car in seventh, the 3 car \Nin eighth, the 2 car in ninth...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.93,0:16:01.98,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The 11 car in 10th, the 10 car in 11th.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.98,0:16:07.98,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Then comes the Yashi-Kita Gang, \Nwith the 16 in 12th and the 18 in 13th.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.98,0:16:09.78,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,And then, a bit farther back...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.60,0:16:15.06,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Well, here's a surprise. \NThe 86 has made it up into 14th place!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.28,0:16:20.83,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The Civic is right behind him in 15th.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.25,0:16:25.21,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,And now, all 15 racers \Nhave entered Sector 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.52,0:16:30.60,Top Italics,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,I legitimately didn't expect \Nto see the 86 advancing like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.38,0:16:36.03,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Fighting against a field like this \Nin an 86 is totally reckless.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.40,0:16:41.77,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it already a miracle\N that Kanata's not last?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.65,0:16:53.19,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,I've caught up and I'm in an ideal \Nposition. Best seat in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.66,0:16:58.36,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,It's a sick joke that he was faster than\N Beckenbauer before the Kamaboko Straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.72,0:17:01.80,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,How did an off-the-shelf 86 pull that off?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.62,0:17:07.94,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,If he's got some special trick, \NI'm gonna find out what it is and steal it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.50,0:17:12.55,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,Once I know how to do it,\Nthat's my chance to turn it around, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.50,0:17:25.75,Default,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,He's cornering so fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.25,0:17:30.33,Default,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,But that {\i1}can't{\i0} be right. Our cars \Nshould be in the same category group.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.30,0:17:38.14,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,When I've got the pedal down,\N I'm clearly faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.14,0:17:42.29,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,We might both have 2-liter engines, \Nbut there's a huge gulf between NA and turbo.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.98,0:17:47.92,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,He leaves me for dust under braking.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.17,0:17:49.46,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,His cornering's so fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.90,0:17:56.97,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,I can't let him get away. I need to hang on.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.97,0:18:00.08,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,Just long enough for me to\N floor it! Until I hit a straight!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.20,0:18:03.15,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,It's no good. He's leaving me behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.02,0:18:08.35,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,He's getting away. What just happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.57,0:18:11.21,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,I can't get my head around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.82,0:18:15.64,Italics,Maezono,0000,0000,0000,,It's like we're not subject \Nto the same laws of physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.73,0:18:30.54,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like there's an incident!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.77,0:18:34.88,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The BMW driven by Natsume\N in 10th has slowed right down.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.18,0:18:39.09,Italics,Kakeru,0000,0000,0000,,Lucky us. Our prize money just \Ngot bumped up for no extra work.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.65,0:18:45.68,Default,Nozomi,0000,0000,0000,,Bro! I just saw a red car\N in my rearview mirror!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.97,0:18:47.92,Default,Kakeru,0000,0000,0000,,Damn. He's here already?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.48,0:18:51.65,Default,Kakeru,0000,0000,0000,,The gap we fought hard to \Nbuild up got eaten up in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.89,0:18:54.27,Default,Nozomi,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do? Try a block formation?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.51,0:18:57.99,Default,Kakeru,0000,0000,0000,,No, forget that. \NBlocking him would kill our pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.99,0:19:00.24,Default,Kakeru,0000,0000,0000,,We don't wanna lose \Nmore time to the leaders.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.24,0:19:05.75,Default,Kakeru,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't give him an opportunity, he has \Nno chance of passing us on a road this narrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.70,0:19:08.89,Italics,Kakeru,0000,0000,0000,,Just stick to your ideal line.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.89,0:19:12.54,Default,Nozomi,0000,0000,0000,,Works for me. I'm ready\N to take Kanata on head-on!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.85,0:19:16.50,Italics,Kakeru,0000,0000,0000,,If you do that, you won't stand a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.68,0:19:22.96,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The 3 and the 2 seem to blend \Ntogether as they enter the fog.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.51,0:19:28.52,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The cloud of death around the ghost town \Ndraws car after car into its embrace.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.02,0:19:33.69,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Here in the commentary booth, \Nthis area always makes my heart sink.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.69,0:19:41.18,Default,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,Right. The lack of visibility from the drone \Nfootage makes it hard to tell what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.18,0:19:45.45,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like the Yashi-Kita Gang have \Nthe 86 pinned in as all three charge onwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.42,0:19:52.88,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,So this might be... \NWell, a "good chance" isn't the right phrase,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.88,0:19:56.79,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,but an opportunity to share with you \Nthe information I found on Katagiri.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.50,0:19:59.36,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,He normally goes by Kanata Rivington.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.36,0:20:03.37,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,We can assume the "Katagiri" \Ncomes from his Japanese father.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.15,0:20:06.43,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,He's from Cambridge in England,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.43,0:20:12.06,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,and went to the Royal Donington Park \NRacing School, or RDRS for short.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.73,0:20:16.73,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,He first sat in a kart aged four, and by \Nseven, he was racing them competitively.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.18,0:20:21.53,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Over the next two years, \Nhe racked up six notable British titles.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.08,0:20:26.22,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Aged 10, he entered Formula 4. Two years \Nlater, he had more titles to his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.22,0:20:29.74,Default,Kogashiwa,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, hold on a second.\NThat's an {\i1}incredible{\i0} career.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.07,0:20:31.77,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Are you for real?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.21,0:20:37.34,Flashback,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,There's something fundamentally \Ndifferent about where he's at.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.93,0:20:41.07,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,I thought Shun was just full of crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.33,0:20:48.76,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,It seems there's a mandatory graduation \Nexam for students at this racing school,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.76,0:20:55.00,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,and Katagiri achieved top marks \Nin every "mission" on the curriculum.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.60,0:21:01.28,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,His cumulative score \Napparently set a new school record,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.55,0:21:07.67,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,and RDRS staff excitedly told me how he had \Nan otherworldly knack for shrinking lap times
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.67,0:21:10.90,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,on both the track and in the simulator.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.85,0:21:17.29,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Now, with that kind of talent, he had \Nhis pick of opportunities after graduating.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.51,0:21:23.72,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,But shockingly, he turned them all down, \Nand returned to his family home for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.13,0:21:29.85,Default,Ren Dad,0000,0000,0000,,That would've been around the time \NKatherine took a turn for the worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.06,0:21:33.40,Default,Mayuko,0000,0000,0000,,I think so. He's such a kind boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.95,0:21:39.02,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,But here comes the real surprise \NI uncovered while doing this research.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.74,0:21:46.01,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,There happens to be a Japanese instructor\N on the staff at this academy in Donington.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.90,0:21:47.95,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,And his name is...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.88,0:21:50.53,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Takumi Fujiwara.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.47,0:23:35.62,Italics,Narration,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Turn 06: The Tragic Rallyist.